cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.DB 

This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to extract disease-symptom relationships from medical articles. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and information retrieval. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of co-occurrence analysis and word embeddings suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper involves medical data, which could fall under cs.CY (Computational Biology and Bioinformatics).
